theorem Topology.P1_inter_open_right {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A U : Set X}
    (hP1A : Topology.P1 (X := X) A) (hOpenU : IsOpen U) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) (A ∩ U) := by
  -- unpack the definition of `P1`
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1A ⊢
  intro x hxAU
  -- `x` belongs to both `A` and `U`
  have hxA : x ∈ A := hxAU.1
  have hxU : x ∈ U := hxAU.2
  -- From `P1 A`, `x` lies in `closure (interior A)`
  have hxClIntA : x ∈ closure (interior A) := hP1A hxA
  -- Show first that `x ∈ closure (interior A ∩ U)`
  have hxCl : x ∈ closure (interior A ∩ U) := by
    -- use the neighbourhood characterization of the closure
    refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
    intro V hVopen hxV
    -- consider the open neighbourhood `V ∩ U` of `x`
    have hOpenVU : IsOpen (V ∩ U) := hVopen.inter hOpenU
    have hxVU : x ∈ V ∩ U := And.intro hxV hxU
    -- since `x ∈ closure (interior A)`, this neighbourhood meets `interior A`
    obtain ⟨y, ⟨hyV, hyU⟩, hyIntA⟩ :=
      (mem_closure_iff.1 hxClIntA) (V ∩ U) hOpenVU hxVU
    -- the point `y` lies in `V ∩ (interior A ∩ U)`
    exact ⟨y, by
      -- rearrange the intersection to match the required shape
      simp [Set.inter_assoc, Set.inter_comm] [hyV, hyU, hyIntA]⟩
  -- `interior A ∩ U` is an open subset of `A ∩ U`
  have h_subset :
      (interior A ∩ U : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∩ U) := by
    intro y hy
    -- `interior A` and `U` are both open
    have hOpenSub : IsOpen (interior A ∩ U) :=
      isOpen_interior.inter hOpenU
    -- and contained in `A ∩ U`
    have hSub : (interior A ∩ U : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ U := by
      intro z hz
      exact And.intro (interior_subset hz.1) hz.2
    exact interior_maximal hSub hOpenSub hy
  -- transport the membership of `x` along the inclusions of closures
  have h_closure_subset :
      closure (interior A ∩ U) ⊆ closure (interior (A ∩ U)) :=
    closure_mono h_subset
  exact h_closure_subset hxCl
